<TITLE> Khaleda celebrates Eid free, calls for democracy restored </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 2 (bdnews24.com)  Former prime minister Khaleda Zia, celebrating Eid with supporters and well-wishers after her release from jail last month, called for concerted efforts to restore democracy and put an elected government back in office. "All have to work together to restore democracy and form an elected government. I hope an elected government will rule the country in the future," she told reporters after exchanging Eid greetings on Thursday. The BNP chairperson exchanged Eid greetings with the diplomats, party adherents and people from across the social spectrum from 11 am at Eskaton Ladies Club. The visitors were treated to sweets and Eid delicacies. "My family is not with me today. But I am happy that I am celebrating Eid as a free person." Khaleda spent the previous Eid in the makeshift special jail in the parliament complex, as did her arch political rival former prime minister Sheikh Hasina. Both are facing a slew of corruption charges. "I have three families now  party, my family and countrymen. I am happy to celebrate Eid with the countrymen," she said. She urged the nation to pray for her. "Pray for me so that I can serve you and the country. I was, I am and I will be with you all the time." Later she visited slain husband former president Ziaur Rahman's grave. bdne
